metadata.name: Alpinism #30
metadata.description:
“Only those who will risk going too far can possibly find out how far one can go.” - T.S. Eliot

---

Alpinism is a tribute to the rugged and wild landscapes that rise around us. Which may at once intrigue, impress, intimidate, and inspire.

I am captivated by the mythology of these settings. Where natural shapes appear fantastical. A ridge line drawn by pen meets sky poured out from neon gradient. Where observation is made through the lens of imagination.

Each piece begins with the concept of a mountain landscape. A number of ranges are drawn by pen in one of three styles. Within each style is a spectrum of variation that produces different drawn qualities. The backdrop may be an imagined sky, an impossible sunset, a piece of parchment. A testament to the interpreter’s memory of the scene. 

---
- Made with p5js in the White Mountains of NH July 2022
- press s to save png

metadata.name: Zephyr #311
metadata.description:
The name Zephyr traces back to Zephyrus, the Greek god of the west wind, and refers to any light breeze. The flowing particles get pushed around by a zephyr, creating interesting and organic patterns.

Live Mode Controls:

- Default is 2000x2000 pixel canvas. Press “1” for 1000x1000px canvas, “3” for 3000x3000px, “4” for 4000x4000px
- Press 'p' to save a png of the canvas.

metadata.name: Citta #195
metadata.description:
Citta as mind Citta as city. 

Citta is city of interconnected minds from future of Metropolis IX(Project id:13292), after singularity people uploaded their consciousness into inorganic self-constructing structures. 

There are 13 different mind-hives named with upper case letters, only "MC-00001" is monochrome rest is in color. "SCMB" and "SCCB' are in spiral formation due to their nature.

Press 1 to 8 export PNG 1000px to 8000px 
9 exports 10000px PNG 

Exports are dependent on CPU, so larger export might take time. Please be patient. If you cannot export reach me out.

Works best in Chrome browser. 

Created with p5.js and canvas api.
Murat Atimtay 2022 | @atimtay | www.muratatimtay.com

metadata.name: Orchard #134
metadata.description:
A natural media rendering of a fruit tree during one of the four seasons. Sometimes, you'll catch it at night - with lights strung on the tree!

The amount of color in spring and fall, snow in winter, fruit on and off the tree will all vary. There are four spring bloom palettes, four trunk colors, and seven types of fruit. 

Press ’s’ to save a screenshot. Image size is 1000x1000px
Press ’p’ to pause/resume.

To render a variation at a new size, open live view and append '?size=#' to the end of the URL. The new size may be from 100 to 3,000. This version will not be a 1:1 match to your edition but will have all of the same features.

metadata.name: Hybrid Canvas #84
metadata.description:
Exploration between generative and post-processed / procedural work.

The canvas is created with a number of pre-curated shapes previously created with a custom generative algorithm. Those shapes are post-processed to make the geometrical background.

A secondary algorithm purely generative draws on top of this canvas.

The piece lives in its own space, where lights/shades exist and rotate around. Every minute there's a change in the angle. 24 hours for a full cycle.

Controls:
- touch the piece to increase the intensity of the light/shade
- e: hide the light/shade
- c: change the color of the light/shade
- s: save an HD png screenshot

Original piece by Ismahelio. Made with p5js. Madrid, 2022.

metadata.name: fxpam(face) #1
metadata.description:
Creating this project was a pure chance; When I came upon a project by Pam with PFP faces, I thought to myself the whole process of the paintings could become generative with a few simple rules. Had a constructive conversation with Pam and she helped me generously with describing the basic rules and sending some sketches. Using those, I was able to write this code, creating the faces.

All the elements were created by p5js pure.
